Below is a worked‐through example of how to match and build the displayed structure step by step.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1)  ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET IMAGE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
■ Block Count and Layers

•  Total of 9 blocks.  
•  From the bottom up, one can think of it in about 5 “layers”:  
  – Layer 1 (bottom): Two red arch blocks (left/right) plus one small red cube tucked in between.  
  – Layer 2: One long yellow rectangular block bridging across the arches.  
  – Layer 3–4: Three green cubes (one on the left end of the yellow block, and two stacked on the right end).  
  – Layer 5 (top): One blue cube on top of the right‐hand green stack, finished by one orange triangular wedge as the “roof.”  

■ Spatial Relationships

•  Bottom Layer:
   – The two red arches sit side by side with a small gap in between; the red cube fills that gap behind them.  
•  Middle Layer:
   – The yellow rectangular block is laid horizontally on top of (and spanning across) the two arches and the red cube.  
•  Upper Layers:
   – On the far left of the yellow block sits a single green cube.
   – On the far right, two green cubes are stacked on top of each other.  
   – A blue cube sits atop the second green cube on the right, and finally
     an orange wedge rests on the very top as the “peak.”  

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2)  SELECTING THE REQUIRED DICTIONARY BLOCKS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Below are the **exact** block indices (no rotation allowed beyond what is shown):

1.  Red Arch (left base) → Dictionary index #3  
2.  Red Arch (right base) → Dictionary index #5  
3.  Red Cube (center of base) → Dictionary index #7  
4.  Yellow Rectangular Block (horizontal “beam”) → Dictionary index #10  
5.  Three Green Cubes → Dictionary index #6 used three times  
6.  Blue Cube (on top of green tower) → Dictionary index #8  
7.  Orange Triangular Wedge (roof piece) → Dictionary index #15  

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3)  PROPOSED ASSEMBLY ORDER
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 3   // Left red arch  
  Step2: Move block with index 5   // Right red arch  
  Step3: Move block with index 7   // Red cube, placed between/behind arches  
  Step4: Move block with index 10  // Long yellow block bridging arches  
  Step5: Move block with index 6   // First green cube (left side on top of yellow)  
  Step6: Move block with index 6   // Second green cube (bottom of right stack)  
  Step7: Move block with index 6   // Third green cube (top of right stack)  
  Step8: Move block with index 8   // Blue cube atop the right green stack  
  Step9: Move block with index 15  // Orange triangular wedge on top  
}  

Following these steps (and ensuring each block is used in the orientation shown in the dictionary) will replicate the target structure exactly.
